-- Lender IPF's profit boosted by eastern Europe gains
-- By Abhiram Nandakumar in Bangalore
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 02:28AM EDT
-- None



July 30 (Reuters) - Consumer credit lender International Personal Finance <IPF.L> reported an 11 percent rise in first-half profit as it lent more in Poland and Lithuania during the period.

IPF, which provides small personal loans to 2.6 million borrowers in eastern Europe and Mexico, raised its interim dividend by 10.5 percent to 4.2 pence per share. [ID:nRSd6572Na]